a cdn for myself and possibly friends. reach out if you want to be added!

cdn.neelr.dev

## cli

```bash
curl -fsSL https://cdn.neelr.dev/YeRtsn.sh | bash
```

then:
```bash
cdn --login <your-token>
cdn file.png                # upload (default action)
cdn file.png -e 7d          # upload with 7 day expiry
cdn -l                      # list files
cdn -d <key>                # delete
```

supports files up to 5TB via automatic multipart upload.

## screenshot auto-upload (macos)

automatically upload screenshots and copy link to clipboard:

```bash
cdn --install-screenshot              # watch ~/Desktop (default)
cdn --install-screenshot ~/Screenshots # watch custom folder
cdn --uninstall-screenshot            # remove
cdn --toggle-delete                   # toggle delete after upload (default: on)
cdn --screenshot-pattern "*.png"      # set glob pattern (default: Screenshot*.png)
```

## api

all endpoints require a valid token. see /api for full docs.

POST /api/upload
  upload a file (< 100MB)
  body: multipart/form-data
    - token: string (required)
    - file: file (required)
    - expiry: number (optional, ms until expiration)
  response: { success: true, url: "/abc123.png" }

for files > 100MB, use multipart upload:
  POST /api/upload/init → { uploadId, key }
  POST /api/upload/part (headers: X-Token, X-Upload-Id, X-Upload-Key, X-Part-Number) → { etag }
  POST /api/upload/complete → { url }
  POST /api/upload/abort (cleanup failed uploads)

POST /api/list
  list your files
  body: { "token": "your-token" }
  response: { files: [{ url, originalName, size, uploaded, expires }], isAdmin: bool }

POST /api/delete
  delete a file
  body: { "token": "your-token", "key": "abc123.png" }
  response: { success: true }
